Text: Is this Sergey's hideout?

Yeah. A hidden hideout, separate from his official
one, if you will.
A "hidden hideout"... How redundant...heheh...

So, this one is different from his hideout in the
capital, huh.

We didn't turn up any useful intel in the capital,
so I'm hoping that what we find here will make
up for that.

I understand how you feel, Zeta, but don't be
impatient. Results are never guaranteed in
reconnaissance.

Well, maybe that's how you think of it, but coming
up empty-handed affects my self-cred as head of
espionage.

So just what sort of place is this hideout?
It's half a day's ride on horse from the
capital, which doesn't seem very accessible—
This place smells like HIM!
Him who...?
Malak! I smell his scent!
Calm down, doggie, I wasn't finished yet—

Why search around all slow when a few sniffs could
turn the place up easy, kitty cat?

Because tracking by scent like you dogs is an
absolute last resort for me, not to mention I
make a point of not trusting blindly!

If the enemy knows they've got a therianthrope
spymaster on their trail, the easiest trap for them
to set would be one using scent.

The fact that you don't know even that much shows
just how much of a meatheaded mutt you are.
Hey, kitty cat! You making fun of me?!
Stay!
Awoo...!
That goes for you too, Zeta.
Grrr...

So basically, there may be some secret clue that
connects Sergey and Malak hidden here.

I didn't want to say it outright, but yeah,
pretty much.
...Then let's proceed with caution.

What the...?! What're all these...devices along the
walls?

This material is not simple iron, or even mithril...
Say, Zeta, did you conduct a preliminary
investigation of this place?

Yeah, to the extent that I could. But I found more
questions than answers.

As you said, the substance that the interior is made
from is far from normal, making for quite the
bizarre space.
Is that why you brought us all here to see it?

Correct. Wouldn't be very wise of me to try to
tackle a place like this on my own, now would it?
So you're a scaredy cat.
Yeah, yeah, get it all out while you can.
I assume you've detected potential threats ahead?
I have. And quite a few, at that.

As you'll see, they make the defense golems we've
faced up to this point look like an opening act—
What...?! Why are these here?!
They look like specimens... What is all this?!

All I can say in response to that is, it's exactly
what you think it is.

At a glance, I'd say there's 50 Malaks here. Some
mechanism seems to be keeping them unconscious.

Are they being bred, or kept as research subjects...?
Either way, this is a truly terrifying scene.

If, say, this swarm of Malaks were to be set loose in
Velgalta's capital, the city would descend into chaos
in the blink of an eye.

And if Sergey could exercise the same level of
control over all these as he did back in Madlid, you
can forget simply having bad relations with the Cult—
he may have even been able to rise against them!
The subjects... Completely unknown properties...

Oh, Eta. Word to the wise, but don't go touching
anything—
Hm... I already pushed it.
"Already"?! Why would you do that?!
Grrraaarrrghhh!

Ah, as expected, they moved... They really were...
alive...
Oh, come on!!! Etaaaaaa!!!
Oh, for the love of...! That didn't take long!
Ahaha... In a way, it went just as expected.
Awooooo! Delta the dragon slayer is on the hunt!

Delta! Whatever you do, don't wake up the ones that
are still asleep!

The darkness of this place may be even deeper than
we imagined...!
